    "description": "Bengt Johan Kristofer Benzow was a Swedish lecturer born on March 18th, 1883 in Västra Alstad, Malmöhus. He married Ruth Kleberg in 1918 and had two children: Jan (born 1921) and Märta (born 1926). Benzow earned a Studieexamen degree from Malmö exam school in 1902, Bachelor of Arts degree from Lund University in 1905, Filosofie licentiat degree in 1908, and Bachelor of Theology degree in 1910. He worked at various schools and institutions throughout his career. Apart from teaching, he also wrote a number of books and articles on religious issues and participated in radio lectures on Church and Religious Science. He passed away on unknown date." 
